OL,6,F"It was light enough for me to see the
OL,7,Fnext ship next to us. It had broken in
OL,8,Fhalf and formed a V for about three
OL,9,Fminutes and then both parts of the V
OL,10,Fwent under the water.
OL,12,F"It was a torpedo from a German fast
OL,13,Fpatrol boat."
OL,15,FDestroyers including Serapis laid
OL,16,Fcovering fire for the troops when they
OL,17,Flanded.
